{{Infobox Airline |airline = Air Service Gabon |logo = |logo_size = |fleet_size = 5 |destinations = |IATA = X7 |ICAO = AGB |parent = |company_slogan = |founded = 1965 |headquarters = [[Libreville]], [[Gabon]] |key_people = |hubs = [[Libreville International Airport]] |secondary_hubs = |focus_cities = |frequent_flyer = |lounge = |alliance = |website = http://www.airservice.aero/?id_Sessionlangue=2 }}
'''Air Service Gabon''' was an [[airline]] based in [[Libreville]], [[Gabon]]. It was established in 1965 and operated scheduled flights and passenger and charter services in [[West Africa]]. Its main base was [[Libreville International Airport]].<ref name="FI">{{cite news | title= Directory: World Airlines | work= [[Flight International]] | page= 66 | date= 2007-03-27}}</ref> The company announced that it ceased operation as of August 3, 2010.
The airline is on the [[List of air carriers banned in the European Union]].
== Destinations == Air Service Gabon operated scheduled services to the following destinations (at March 2009):
*[[Cameroon]] **[[Douala]] ([[Douala International Airport]]) *[[Gabon]] **[[Franceville]] ([[M'Vengue El Hadj Omar Bongo Ondimba International Airport]]) **[[Gamba, Gabon|Gamba]] ([[Gamba Airport]]) **[[Koulamoutou]] ([[Koula Moutou Airport]]) **[[Libreville]] ([[Libreville International Airport]]) **[[Makokou]] ([[Makokou Airport]]) **[[Mouila]] ([[Mouila Airport]]) **[[Oyem]] ([[Oyem Airport]]) **[[Port-Gentil]] ([[Port-Gentil International Airport]]) *[[Republic of the Congo]] **[[Brazzaville]] ([[Maya-Maya Airport]]) **[[Pointe-Noire]] ([[Pointe Noire Airport]]) *[[São Tomé and Príncipe]] **[[São Tomé]] ([[São Tomé International Airport]])
==Fleet== [[File:TR-LGC Dash 8-102A Air Service Gabon LPA 10NOV03.jpg|thumb|A Dash 8-100 at La Palma in 2003.]] The Air Service Gabon fleet consisted of the following aircraft (as of 15 November 2009) [http://www.ch-aviation.ch/aircraft.php?search=set&airline=G8&al_op=1]:
*4 [[de Havilland Canada Dash 8|Bombardier Dash 8-100]] *1 [[de Havilland Canada Dash 8|Bombardier Dash 8-300]]
As of 4 November 2008, the average age of the Air Service Gabon fleet is 12.3 years ([http://www.airfleets.net/ageflotte/Air%20Service%20Gabon.htm]).
