{{Orphan|date=September 2011}}
'''Animal Rescue Sofia''' is a [[non-governmental organization]] (NGO) founded and registered in [[Sofia, Bulgaria]]. The organization is actively working to solve the issue with the homeless animals in [[Bulgaria]]. Its lies in the largest Bulgarian online dog forum – www.dog.bg.
Currently, Animal Rescue Sofia manages the largest dog shelter in Bulgaria – the Bogrov dog shelter, near Sofia. The organization takes care of 500 dogs there. Also ARS is running a free [[Animal neutering|spay/neuter clinic]] at the shelter and is running [[Animal adoption]] programs in Bulgaria as well as the [[Netherlands]] and [[Germany]].
Unfortunately their three-year lease expires in December 2013 and cannot be renewed. After investigating all other alternatives, Animal Rescue Sofia is now fundraising in order to purchase a nearby farm which has the right location, buildings and infrastructure for housing all the remaining animals and creating a model new shelter.<ref>http://www.arsofia.com/shelter</ref>
The foundation is funded almost entirely by private and corporate donations.
