{{EngvarB|date=March 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=March 2016}} {{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}} {{Infobox radio station | name = Asyik FM | image = Asyik FM Logo.PNG | city = [[Kuala Lumpur]] | area = [[West Malaysia]] | branding = | slogan = Moi Num Moi | frequency = Varies depending on its region | translator = | repeater = | airdate = <!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes}} --> | last airdate = <!-- for defunct stations --> | share = | share as of = | share source = | format = [[Talk radio|Talk]], [[contemporary hit radio]] | language = [[Aslian languages|Aslian]], [[Malay language|Malay]] | power = | erp = | haat = | class = | facility_id = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord|}} --> | callsign_meaning = | former_callsigns = | former_frequencies = <!-- use – --> | affiliations = | owner = [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]] | licensee = | sister_stations = Bintulu FM, [[Johor FM]], IKIM.fm, Kedah FM, Kelantan FM, Keningau FM, [[KL FM]], Labuan FM, Langkawi FM, Limbang FM, [[Malacca FM]], Miri FM, [[Mutiara FM]], [[Negeri FM]], [[Pahang FM]], Perak FM, Perlis FM, RaSa FM, Red FM, Sabah FM, Sabah Vfm, Sandakan FM, [[Sarawak FM]], [[Selangor FM]], Sibu FM, Tawau FM, Terengganu FM, UFM and Wai FM | webcast = | website = {{URL|http://asyikfm.rtm.gov.my/}} }}
'''Asyik FM''' is an [[Orang Asli]] radio channel operated by [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia]]. On 1 January 2007, Asyik FM broadcast from 8 am to 10 pm, but as of 31 August 2011, it now broadcasts from 8:00am to 11:00pm.
== Etymology == The station is formerly known as Radio 7 and Radio Malaysia Channel 7.
== Frequencies == * 91.1&nbsp;MHz from Kuala Lumpur Tower covers Klang Valley (Kuala Lumpur) * 102.5&nbsp;MHz from Gunung Ulu Kali covers Selangor, Putrajaya, West Pahang (Bentong, Temerloh, Raub, Jerantut, Bera, Kuala Lipis, Jerantut, Jengka, Maran, and Merapoh), South Perak (Sungkai, Trolak, Slim River, Tanjung Malim), Negeri Sembilan (Nilai, Mantin, Simpang Durian, parts of Seremban/Rembau/Port Dickson/Jelebu/Jempol) and parts of North Malacca (Masjid Tanah and Lubuk Cina) * 105.1&nbsp;MHz from Gunung Brinchang covers Cameron Highlands, and Ulu Kinta Perak * 95.6&nbsp;MHz from Gunung Ledang covers Johor (Segamat, Kluang, Batu Pahat, Muar, Ledang), parts of Malacca (Jasin, Merlimau, Bemban, Nyalas, Asahan, Batang Melaka), Southern parts of Negeri Sembilan (Gemencheh, Gemas, Ayer Kurning Selatan and Rompin) and Southwest Pahang (Bandar Muadzam Shah and Bandar Tun Abdul Razak/Keratong) * 97.3&nbsp;MHz from Bukit Ladang Teh covers Lenggong, Sauk, Kuala Kangsar and part of Gerik * 99.9&nbsp;MHz from Bukit Botak covers Damak * SW 6050&nbsp;kHz (Nationwide, transmitted from RTM Kajang)
