The '''Embassy of the Republic of Serbia in Moscow''' ({{lang-ru|Посольство Республики Сербия в Москве}}, {{lang-sr|Амбасада Републике Србије у Москви}}) is the [[diplomatic mission]] of [[Serbia]] in the [[Russian Federation]]. It is located at 46 [[Mosfilmovskaya Street]] ({{lang-ru|Мосфильмовская ул., 46}}) in the [[Ramenki District]] of [[Moscow]]<ref>{{cite web | title = Russian Federation | publisher = [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Serbia)]] | url = http://www.mfa.gov.rs/Embassies/moskva/moskva_e.html | accessdate = 2008-06-27 }}</ref> Current Ambassador of Serbia to Russia is [[Slavenko Terzić]].
In 2011, the embassy was attacked by [[National Bolshevik Party]] activists.<ref>[http://www.newspepper.su/news/2011/5/27/embassy-of-serbia-in-moscow-have-taken-under-heavy-guard/ Embassy of Serbia in Moscow have taken under heavy guard]</ref><ref>[http://b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2011&mm=05&dd=27&nav_id=74596 Black paint thrown at Serbian embassy in Moscow] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110531012425/http://www.b92.net/eng/news/politics-article.php?yyyy=2011&mm=05&dd=27&nav_id=74596 |date=2011-05-31 }}</ref>
