The '''flag of [[Bago Region]]''' depicts a [[Hamsa (bird)|hamsa]] on a blue background. The name "Bago Division" ({{my|ပဲခူးတိုင်း}}) is written underneath the bird, despite the region no longer bearing that name. The former [[flag of Mon State]] is very similar to the flag of Bago Region, but its hamsa and text have different proportions and designs.

In local legend, the [[Bago, Myanmar|city of Bago]] was established on the location where a hamsa sought refuge during a massive flood, hence the adoption of the bird on the flag.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Kuipers |first1=Ludo |title=Bago Region {{!}} Flag {{!}} Myanmar {{!}} OzOutback |url=https://ozoutback.com.au/Myanmar/flags/slides/14_Bago_Region.html |website=ozoutback.com.au |accessdate=9 July 2018}}</ref>

