==Pakistan== {{Main|Pakistani meat dishes#Kebabs|Pakistani cuisine}} {| class="wikitable sortable" width="100%" ! Name ! class="unsortable"| Image ! Description |- | [[Chapli kebab]] | [[File:Chapli Kebab.jpg|127px]] | A delicacy of [[Pakistan]] from [[Khyber Pakhtunkhwa]] province – marinated beef in spices and deep fried flat.<ref>{{cite book | last=Raichlen | first=S. | last2=Fink | first2=B. | title=The Barbecue! Bible | publisher=Workman Pub. | year=2008 | isbn=978-0-7611-4943-9 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=JWoOI6MASqwC&pg=PA226 | access-date=May 26, 2017 | page=226}}</ref> In Pakistan, it is sometimes deep fried in animal [[tallow]], and it is a common kebab.{{efn|"In Pakistan, animal tallow is used as commercial deep-frying agent for the traditional food chapli kebab. The chapli and shami kabab are considered as one of the most commercially available traditional dishes of people living in Pakistan, ..."<ref>{{cite book | last=Pakistan | first=Chemical Society of | title=Journal of the Chemical Society of Pakistan | publisher=Chemical Society of Pakistan. | issue=v. 30, nos. 5-6 | year=2008 | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=CG4cAQAAMAAJ | access-date=May 26, 2017|page=750}}</ref>}} |- | ''[[Lola kabab]]/[[Gola kabab]]'' | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|127px]] --> | Kabab of [[Pakistan]] and [[Afghanistan]] – rolled meatballs originating in [[Peshawar]] and [[Kandahar]].{{citation needed|date=June 2018}} |- | [[Seekh kebab]] | [[Image:Pakistani Food Beef Kabobs.jpg|127px]] | Prepared with [[Ground meat|minced meat]] with spices and grilled on skewers. It is cooked in a [[Tandoor]], and is often served with [[chutney]]s or [[Mentha|mint]] sauce. A seekh kebab can also be served in a naan bread much like döner kebab. |- | [[Shami kebab]] | [[File:4th October 2012 Shami Kebab.jpg|127px]] | Made of minced meat, with paste of lentils and chopped onion and coriander and green chillies usually added to the mixture, which is kneaded in a disc-like shape and fried. Best results are obtained when fried in [[ghee]]. In some places, a binding agent is used to keep the kabab together. |- | [[Malai tikka]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|127px]] --> | Chunks or strips of chicken marinated in a white yoghurt and garlic sauce and grilled.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}} |- | [[Reshmi kebab]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|127px]] --> | Minced chicken adequately seasoned and then barbecued on a charcoal grill.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}} |- | [[Bihari kebab]] | <!--[[File:EXAMPLE|127px]] --> | Chunks or strips of lean beef, marinated in a spicy yoghurt/chilli marinade and tenderized to perfection before slowly grilled on a charcoal flame.{{citation needed|date=June 2018}} |}
