==Romania== {{Main|Romanian cuisine}} {| class="wikitable sortable" width="100%" ! Name ! class="unsortable"| Image ! Description |- |[[Frigărui]] |[[File:Frigărui.jpg|127px]] |Small pieces of meat (usually pork, beef, mutton, lamb or chicken) grilled on a skewer, very similar to [[shashlik]],<ref name="encyclopedia"> {{cite book | author=Marks | first=Gil | title=Encyclopedia of Jewish Food | url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gFK_yx7Ps7cC&q=kebab%20denotesanarray | year=2010 | publisher=Houghton Mifflin Harcourt | isbn=978-0-544-18631-6}}</ref> or [[shish kebab]]. Often, the pieces of meat alternate with bacon, sausages, or vegetables, such as onions, tomatoes, bell peppers and mushrooms. It is seasoned with spices such as pepper, garlic, savory, rosemary, marjoram and laurel. |}
