{{Infobox language |name=Luba-Katanga |nativename=Kiluba |states=[[Democratic Republic of Congo]] |region=[[Katanga Province]] |speakers=1,505,000 |date=1991 |ref=e17 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] |fam6=[[Luban languages|Luban]] |fam7=[[Luba languages]] |iso1=lu |iso2=lub |iso3=lub |guthrie=L.33 }}
'''Luba-Katanga''', also known as '''Luba-Shaba''' and '''''Kiluba''''', is one of the two major [[Bantu language]]s spoken in the [[Democratic Republic of the Congo]] called "Luba". (See [[Luba-Kasai]].) It is spoken mostly in the south-east area of the country by the [[Luba people]].<ref>{{cite book | last=Batibo | first=Herman | title=Language Decline and Death in Africa | publisher=Multilingual Matters | pages=74 | url=https://books.google.co.uk/books?id=yoZ_fU_B0KgC | isbn=1-85359-808-9 }}</ref>
Kiluba is spoken in the area around [[Kabongo, Democratic Republic of the Congo|Kabongo]], [[Kamina]], [[Luena, Moxico Province|Luena]], [[Lubudi Territory|Lubudi]], [[Malemba-Nkulu Territory|Malemba Nkulu]], Mulongo, and [[Kaniama Territory|Kaniama]], mostly in [[Katanga Province|Katanga]]. Some 500 years ago or more, the Luba Kasai left Katanga and settled in the [[Kasai region|Kasai]]; since then, Luba Kasai (Chiluba) has evolved until it is no longer mutually intelligible with Luba Katanga.
== References == <references/> *{{cite book|author=Samuel Phillips Verner|title=Mukanda wa Chiluba|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HmMvAAAAYAAJ|accessdate=26 August 2012|year=1899|publisher=Spottiswoode}}
==External links== * [http://www.ethnologue.com/show_language.asp?code=lub ''Ethnologue'' report on Luba-Katanga]
