The '''Vatican Telephone Service''' was first officially established in 1930.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.encyclopedia.com/topic/Vatican_City.aspx |title=Vatican City |publisher=[[encyclopedia.com]] |accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref> In 2002, it became part of the Governorate's Department of Telecommunication and oversees all telecommunications needs of [[Vatican City]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vaticanstate.va/content/vaticanstate/en/servizi/servizio-telefoni.html |title=Vatican Telephone Service |publisher=[[Vatican City State]] |accessdate=30 September 2015}}</ref>

The [[telephone code]]/[[List of country calling codes|country code]] for Vatican City is +379. However, it is not currently in use.

